  "time_ut": 1660565104,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dc0 \u0d96\u0dc2\u0db0 03 \u0d9a\u0dca \u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dd3\u0dba\u0dc0 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0db3\u0db4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "03 new drugs to market locally",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Health Minister Dr. Keheliya Rambukwella points out that the plan to produce 40% of the medicines needed in the country is currently being implemented and the target of 20% has been achieved by now.",
        "The minister said that it will be possible to save a lot of money spent on importing medicines through this, and that this will provide a high resolution to the ongoing dollar crisis.",
        "The Minister said this in a program held at the premises of the State Pharmaceutical Manufacturing Corporation in Ratmalana on the occasion of the release of three new medicines to the market.",
        "Levothyroxin 50 mcg for thyroxine deficiency, Omeprazole 20 mg capsules for preventing gastric acidity and Mefenamic Acid 50 mg tablets for pain relief were officially released in the open market today. The State Pharmaceutical Manufacturing Corporation points out that this is a great achievement in the field of pharmaceutical production in this country.",
        "The officials of the State Pharmaceutical Manufacturing Corporation informed the Minister of Health about the existing problems in the production of medicines in this country as well as the targeted program and the Minister advised the officials to pay more attention to achieve the proper goals of the production of medicines needed by the country by solving the deficiencies promptly.",
        "He also pointed out that the government has given priority to importing essential raw materials for the production of medicines in Sri Lanka and many programs are already being undertaken to achieve the future goals. In the face of the current crisis in the country, unnecessary supply chains are at great risk, but more attention has been paid to the health sector. The minister said that nothing can equal the impact of the lack of medicines on the patients and therefore the government's attention for the health services of the people of the country will not be reduced in any way.",
        "The minister pointed out that if all the medicines needed by the country can be produced locally, it will be a great achievement and the responsibility of the State Pharmaceutical Manufacturing Corporation is paramount.",
        "The Minister said that the medicines needed for clinical and outpatients in government hospitals are currently being produced locally in large quantities and it is hoped to continue to increase it."
      ],
